---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const effective = '12 July 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="What ahoosh.ai collects — including personality and leadership assessment answers — where it goes, why, and your GDPR rights. Plain English, no legalese walls."
>
  <section class="legal-hero">
    <div class="legal-wrap">
      <span class="legal-eyebrow">AHoosh.ai — Legal</span>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <span class="legal-effective">Effective: {effective}</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-body">
    <div class="legal-wrap">
      <article>

        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>AHoosh ("we") is operated by Hesam Jafarzadeh, Belgrade, Serbia. This page explains what data ahoosh.ai collects, where it goes, why, and what you can do about it. If anything is unclear, one email answers it: <a class="inline" href="mailto:contact@ahoosh.ai">contact@ahoosh.ai</a>.</p>

        <div class="legal-note legal-note--flag">
          <p><strong>Read this first — the assessments collect sensitive data.</strong> This site runs personality and leadership assessments (Big Five / IPIP-50, DISC, decision-making style, self-esteem, self-efficacy, optimism). Your answers and the resulting profile are <strong>psychological and behavioural data</strong>, which the GDPR treats as sensitive. We only collect them because you chose to take a test, we only store them if you give us your email at the end, and we never use them to make a decision about you.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>What we collect</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Personality and leadership assessment answers and results</strong> — every question you answered, the scores we calculate, your dimension breakdown, and the written interpretation generated for you.</li>
          <li><strong>Business diagnostic answers</strong> — what you enter into the business assessment and the Business Q&amp;A tool.</li>
          <li><strong>Website URL and scan results</strong> — the address you submit to the website assessment or SEO tool, plus what the scan finds.</li>
          <li><strong>Email address and optional name</strong> — when you ask to see or receive your results, or when you use the contact form.</li>
          <li><strong>Contact form details</strong> — name, email, company, what you are looking for, and your message.</li>
          <li><strong>Technical and security data</strong> — your IP address, which Cloudflare logs to protect the site and which is stored alongside an assessment record when one is saved.</li>
          <li><strong>Live chat messages</strong> — if you use the chat widget, the conversation is handled by Tawk.to.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>That is the full list. We run <strong>no advertising trackers</strong>, and we <strong>never sell or share your data</strong> — to anyone, for any reason.</p>

        <h2>The assessments — plainly</h2>
        <p><strong>They are a self-reflection tool, not a diagnosis.</strong> The personality and leadership assessments are informational. They are <strong>not clinical, not psychiatric, and not a diagnostic instrument</strong>. They do not identify any condition, and we never use them to make a decision about you — no screening, no hiring, no scoring you as a customer, no automated decision-making of any kind.</p>
        <p><strong>Nothing is stored until you give us your email.</strong> You can take any assessment and hit "Skip and view results" — in that case nothing about you leaves your browser. When you enter your email to see or receive the full result, that is the moment your answers, scores, and profile get stored and sent to you.</p>
        <p><strong>Explicit consent is the basis.</strong> Submitting your email on the results screen is your explicit consent to us storing your assessment answers and results and emailing them to you. You can withdraw it any time, and we delete everything.</p>

        <h2>Where your data goes</h2>
        <p>These are every processor we use. There are no others.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — hosts the site, protects it (security logs, bot checks on the contact form), and runs our database (D1) where assessment records are stored.</li>
          <li><strong>Cloudflare Workers AI</strong> — generates the written read of your personality results. Your scores and answers are sent to it to produce that text.</li>
          <li><strong>Anthropic (Claude)</strong> — generates the business report and Business Q&amp;A answers. Your assessment inputs are sent to it to produce that report.</li>
          <li><strong>Brevo</strong> — sends your results email and holds our email list. Your address only lands on the list when you submit it on the results screen.</li>
          <li><strong>Resend</strong> — sends the transactional emails from the contact form (our notification and your auto-reply).</li>
          <li><strong>Google PageSpeed Insights</strong> — the website scan sends the URL you enter to Google's public API to measure the page. It is a URL, not personal data, unless you type a personal one.</li>
          <li><strong>Tawk.to</strong> — the live chat widget on our pages.</li>
          <li><strong>Google Fonts</strong> — our fonts load from Google, which means Google sees your IP when a page loads.</li>
          <li><strong>Lemon Squeezy</strong> — our merchant of record once purchases go live. They process payments on their own systems; <strong>your card details never touch us</strong>.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>One human also sees your assessment: <strong>Hesam</strong>. Your results email is copied to him so he can give you a useful read if you ask for one. No ad networks, no data brokers, no resale.</p>

        <h2>Why we are allowed to process it</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Explicit consent</strong> — for the assessment answers and results, and for any email we send you. You give it by submitting your email; you can take it back at any time.</li>
          <li><strong>Legitimate interest</strong> — for security logs and keeping the site running.</li>
          <li><strong>Contract</strong> — when you buy something, we process what is needed to deliver it.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Assessment answers and results</strong> — kept while they are still useful to you (so you can revisit them and so we can advise you if you ask). <strong>Deleted on request</strong> — one email, no questions.</li>
          <li><strong>Contact messages</strong> — as long as needed to reply and follow up, then deleted.</li>
          <li><strong>Email list</strong> — until you unsubscribe or ask us to remove you.</li>
          <li><strong>Security logs</strong> — a short rolling window, on Cloudflare's schedule.</li>
          <li><strong>Purchase records</strong> — as long as tax and accounting law requires, no longer.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>Under the GDPR you can ask us for:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access</strong> — a copy of everything we hold on you, assessment answers included.</li>
          <li><strong>Rectification</strong> — correction of anything wrong.</li>
          <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — deletion of your data, including your assessment record.</li>
          <li><strong>Restriction</strong> and <strong>objection</strong> — tell us to stop processing.</li>
          <li><strong>Portability</strong> — your data in a machine-readable file.</li>
          <li><strong>Withdrawal of consent</strong> — at any time, without giving a reason. Withdrawing it does not affect what was lawful before you withdrew.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="legal-note">
          <p>One email to <a class="inline" href="mailto:contact@ahoosh.ai">contact@ahoosh.ai</a> does all of it. No forms, no hoops — tell us what you want and we handle it.</p>
        </div>
        <p>You also have the right to <strong>complain to a data-protection supervisory authority</strong> — in the EU, the authority in the country where you live or work; in Serbia, the Commissioner for Information of Public Importance and Personal Data Protection.</p>

        <h2>Children</h2>
        <p>This site is not directed at anyone under 18. The assessments are built for adults in a business context, and we do not knowingly collect data from children. If you believe a child has sent us data, email us and we delete it.</p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>If this policy changes, we update this page and the effective date at the top. The current version always lives here. This version is effective <strong>{effective}</strong>.</p>

      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-wrap { max-width: 780px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }

  .legal-hero { padding: 150px 0 20px; position: relative; z-index: 2; }
  .legal-eyebrow {
    display: block; margin-bottom: 18px;
    font-family: var(--font-head); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .22em; font-size: .66rem; color: var(--gold);
  }
  .legal-hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-head); font-weight: 800;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem); line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -.01em; color: var(--silver); margin: 0;
  }
  .legal-effective {
    display: inline-block; margin-top: 22px;
    font-family: var(--font-head); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .18em; font-size: .66rem; color: var(--gold-light);
    border: 1px solid rgba(215,161,61,.35); border-radius: 40px; padding: 9px 20px;
  }

  .legal-body { padding: 26px 0 110px; position: relative; z-index: 2; }
  .legal-body p { color: var(--silver-dim); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.85; margin: 0 0 22px; }
  .legal-body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-head); font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -.01em;
    color: var(--silver); margin: 56px 0 18px;
  }
  .legal-body h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .legal-body ul { list-style: none; margin: 0 0 26px; padding: 0; }
  .legal-body li {
    position: relative; color: var(--silver-dim); font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.85; padding-left: 26px; margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .legal-body li::before {
    content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: .72em;
    width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--gold);
  }
  .legal-body strong { color: var(--silver); font-weight: 600; }
  .legal-body a.inline {
    color: var(--gold-light); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(215,161,61,.4);
    transition: color .3s, border-color .3s;
  }
  .legal-body a.inline:hover { color: var(--silver); border-color: var(--silver); }

  .legal-note {
    border: 1px solid rgba(240,242,245,.12); border-radius: 14px;
    background: rgba(7,22,40,.55); padding: 22px 26px; margin: 30px 0;
  }
  .legal-note p { margin: 0; font-size: .97rem; }
  .legal-note--flag { border-color: rgba(215,161,61,.35); background: rgba(215,161,61,.06); }

  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .legal-wrap { padding: 0 20px; }
    .legal-hero { padding: 120px 0 16px; }
    .legal-body { padding: 20px 0 80px; }
  }
</style>
